[normal]have requested a note explaining
[normal] why HCA was guaranteeing payments under loan obligations f
[normal]or Home Group.
[normal] 
[normal]By way of background
[normal],
[normal] on 
[normal] 6 May 1987
[normal] a predecessor body of the Agency
[normal],
[normal] together with 19 other public sector bodies jointly and severally guaranteed the payment of interest and capital in respect of up to £100m of 8.75% guaranteed loan stock 
[normal]of Home Group. The Agency’s currently assessed share of this contingent liability is 21.65%, and the repayment of capital is due in 2037. The guarantee was issued with the 
[normal]then 
[normal]Secretary of State’s consent.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]D
[normal]etails can be found in HCA’s own Annual Report 
[normal]and Financial Statement
[normal]s 2012/13
[normal] 
